","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Owain","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: shortened form of   O'Callaghan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Callaghan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam, Dermot, Donal, Kiernan, Niall, Conor, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Siobhan, Tiernan.","Irish (Cork): from Gaelic <b>Ó Ceallacháin</b>, see   Callahan  ."]}]},{"name":"Owain","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Perhaps derived in the Roman period from the Latin name <i>Eugenius</i> (  see  <b>Eugene</b>   ); alternatively, possibly from an Old Celtic name meaning ‘born of Esos’. Esos (or Aesos) was a Celtic god known to have been the subject of a cult in ancient Gaul."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gruffydd","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: The Welsh name; from creffydd, strong faith, or strong in faith. Gruffydd, a Welsh form of Gryffydd."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Owain ap Gruffydd ap Owain was born about 1290, in Carmarthenshire, Wales, his father, Gruffydd foel ap Gruffydd, was 42 and his mother, Anne verch Robert, was 42. He had at least 1 son with Joan verch Ieuan."},"et":{"about 1290–":"umbes 1290–Surnud","1279–1320":"1279–1320","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1292–Female":"1292–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1250–1289":"1250–1289","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1279":"1279","about 1290":"umbes 1290","1289":"1289","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"umbes 1310","1250":"1250","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"about 1290–":"noin 1290–Kuollut","1279–1320":"1279–1320","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1292–Female":"1292–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1250–1289":"1250–1289","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1279":"1279","about 1290":"noin 1290","1289":"1289","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"noin 1310","1250":"1250","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"about 1290–":"environ 1290–Décédé","1279–1320":"1279–1320","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1292–Female":"1292–Décédée","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1250–1289":"1250–1289","1250–Female":"1250–Décédée","1279":"1279","about 1290":"environ 1290","1289":"1289","1310":"1310","1320":"1320","about 1310":"environ 1310","1250":"1250","1292":"1292","1290":"1290","Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Owain ap Gruffydd ap Owain est né environ 1290, à Carmarthenshire, Galles, son père, Gruffydd foel ap Gruffydd, avait